PATIENT REQUIREMENTS — CPT/HCPCS CODE ELIGIBILITY REFERENCE
============================================================

This document lists every billing code the system must evaluate, the
eligibility criteria for each, required data inputs, time thresholds,
reimbursement rates, and exclusion rules.

Rates reflect 2025 Medicare Physician Fee Schedule national averages.


────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
APCM — ADVANCED PRIMARY CARE MANAGEMENT
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Key rule: APCM has no time requirement. One level per patient per month.
Cannot be billed with CCM, HHO, or Hospice in the same month. Requires
a population health management platform.


G0556 — Level 1 (Low Complexity)
Rate: $15.20 / month

  - Eligibility: Any Medicare patient with 0–1 chronic conditions
  - Data needed: Chronic condition count from problem list
  - Time requirement: None
  - Exclusions: Cannot bill if CCM, HHO, or Hospice codes are billed
    same month


G0557 — Level 2 (Moderate Complexity)
Rate: $48.84 / month

  - Eligibility: Medicare patient with 2+ chronic conditions
  - Data needed: Chronic condition count from problem list (must be ≥2)
  - Time requirement: None
  - Exclusions: Cannot bill if CCM, HHO, or Hospice codes are billed
    same month. Patient must NOT be QMB (otherwise G0558 applies).


G0558 — Level 3 (High Complexity — QMB)
Rate: $107.07 / month

  - Eligibility: Qualified Medicare Beneficiary (QMB) with 2+ chronic
    conditions
  - Data needed: QMB status from insurance/eligibility data + chronic
    condition count ≥2
  - Time requirement: None
  - Exclusions: Cannot bill if CCM, HHO, or Hospice codes are billed
    same month
  - QMB verification: To bill this code, QMB status must be confirmed
    by either viewing the patient's insurance card or prompting the
    practice to verify the patient's QMB status. Without verified QMB
    status, the patient defaults to G0557 (Level 2).


────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
CCM — CHRONIC CARE MANAGEMENT
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Key rule: CCM requires 2+ chronic conditions expected to last 12+
months. Two mutually exclusive tracks:

  Staff track (99490/99439) — uses clinical staff time
  Provider track (99491/99437) — uses physician/NP time

You pick one track per patient per month — never mix. Cannot bill with
APCM, HHO, or Hospice.


STAFF TRACK
-----------

99490 — Staff Base (Non-Complex CCM)
Rate: $60.49 / month

  - Eligibility: Patient with 2+ chronic conditions expected to last
    12+ months
  - Time requirement: ≥20 minutes of clinical staff time per calendar
    month
  - Data needed: Staff minutes from EHR notes (context-based
    extraction) + chronic condition count
  - Who performs: Clinical staff under general physician supervision
  - Exclusions: Cannot bill with 99491/99437 (provider track) or
    APCM/HHO/Hospice


99439 — Staff Add-on (Each Additional 20 Minutes)
Rate: $45.93 / unit

  - Eligibility: Can only bill as add-on to 99490
  - Time requirement: Each additional 20 minutes of clinical staff
    time beyond the base 20
  - Max units: 2 per month (total staff time cap: 60 minutes billable)
  - Data needed: Total staff minutes.
    Units = floor((staffMin − 20) / 20), max 2


PROVIDER TRACK
--------------

99491 — Provider Base (Physician/NP Performed)
Rate: $82.16 / month

  - Eligibility: Patient with 2+ chronic conditions expected to last
    12+ months
  - Time requirement: ≥30 minutes of physician/NP/PA time per calendar
    month
  - Data needed: Provider minutes from EHR notes (context-based
    extraction) + chronic condition count
  - Who performs: Physician, NP, or PA personally
  - Exclusions: Cannot bill with 99490/99439 (staff track) or
    APCM/HHO/Hospice


99437 — Provider Add-on (Each Additional 30 Minutes)
Rate: $57.58 / unit

  - Eligibility: Can only bill as add-on to 99491
  - Time requirement: Each additional 30 minutes of provider time
    beyond the base 30
  - Max units: 2 per month (total provider time cap: 90 minutes
    billable)
  - Data needed: Total provider minutes.
    Units = floor((drMin − 30) / 30), max 2


────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
HHO — HOME HEALTH OVERSIGHT
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Key rule: Patient must be actively receiving home health services.
Certification codes (G0180/G0179) and supervision (G0181) CAN be billed
in the same month. Cannot bill with APCM, CCM, or Hospice.


G0180 — Initial Home Health Certification
Rate: $53.48 / episode

  - Eligibility: Patient starting a new home health episode (not
    receiving HH in prior 60 days)
  - Data needed: Home health enrollment status from notes + new episode
    confirmation
  - Data source: EHR clinical notes — identify new HH episode start,
    agency certification
  - Frequency: Once per new episode


G0179 — Home Health Recertification
Rate: $41.40 / recertification

  - Eligibility: Patient continuing home health services past initial
    60-day episode
  - Data needed: Home health enrollment status + NOT a new episode
  - Data source: EHR clinical notes — identify ongoing HH services,
    recertification
  - Frequency: Every 60 days for continued episodes


G0181 — Monthly Home Health Supervision
Rate: $106.24 / month

  - Eligibility: Active home health enrollment + physician oversight
    time ≥30 min/month
  - Time requirement: ≥30 minutes physician time supervising the HH
    plan of care
  - Data needed: Home health enrollment from notes + provider minutes
    from notes
  - Stacking: Can be billed alongside G0180 or G0179 in the same month


────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
HOSPICE — HOSPICE CARE OVERSIGHT
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

G0182 — Hospice Care Plan Supervision
Rate: $106.24 / month

  - Eligibility: Patient enrolled in a Medicare-approved hospice
    program
  - Time requirement: ≥30 minutes physician time supervising hospice
    plan of care per month
  - Data needed: Hospice enrollment from EHR notes + provider minutes
    from notes
  - Data source: EHR clinical notes — identify hospice agency
    enrollment, physician oversight documentation
  - Exclusions: Cannot bill with APCM, CCM, or HHO in the same month


────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
CONCURRENT BILLING EXCLUSION MATRIX
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

The system must enforce these restrictions. No two blocked programs can
appear on the same patient in the same calendar month.

             APCM    CCM Staff   CCM Provider   HHO     Hospice
  APCM        —      Blocked     Blocked        Blocked Blocked
  CCM Staff   Blocked —          Blocked        Blocked Blocked
  CCM Prov    Blocked Blocked    —              Blocked Blocked
  HHO         Blocked Blocked    Blocked        —       Blocked
  Hospice     Blocked Blocked    Blocked        Blocked —

Exception within HHO: G0180/G0179 (certification) and G0181 (monthly
supervision) CAN be billed together in the same month. They are within
the same program, not across programs.
